  "handbook.title": "User Manual",
  "handbook.subtitle": "Simple guide for Backup Pro.",
  "handbook.section00": "<h3 class=\"text-xl font-black text-emerald-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center gap-3\"><span class=\"text-2xl\">üöÄ</span> 00 Getting Started & Workflow</h3><div class=\"space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed\"><div class=\"bg-black/20 p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/5\"><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong class=\"text-white\">Welcome!</strong> Backup Pro is designed so that you immediately find everything important. On the left menu you see the 5 areas:</p><ul class=\"list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-xs text-slate-400 marker:text-emerald-500\"><li><strong class=\"text-white\">01 CENTRAL:</strong> Your main overview. Start backups here and see if everything is okay.</li><li><strong class=\"text-white\">02 RESTORE:</strong> Restore deleted files here.</li><li><strong class=\"text-white\">03 CLOUD:</strong> If you also want to store your data in the cloud (optional).</li><li><strong class=\"text-white\">04 ANALYTICS:</strong> Helps you clean up duplicate files.</li><li><strong class=\"text-white\">05 PARAMETERS:</strong> The settings. Here you define WHAT is backed up and WHERE it is stored.</li></ul></div><div><h4 class=\"font-bold text-white text-base mb-3 border-b border-white/10 pb-2\">Your first backup in 3 minutes:</h4><ol class=\"list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-300 marker:text-emerald-500 marker:font-bold\"><li>Click on <strong class=\"text-emerald-400\">05 PARAMETERS</strong> on the left.</li><li>Under \"Source Path\": Choose a <strong>folder</strong> (üìÅ), a <strong>single file</strong> (üìÑ) or <strong>multiple files</strong> (üìë).</li><li>Under \"Target Path\": Choose where the backup should be stored (e.g. USB stick).</li><li>Click the big button <strong class=\"text-white bg-blue-600/20 px-2 py-0.5 rounded border border-blue-500/30\">Save parameters persistently</strong> at the bottom.</li><li>Go back to <strong class=\"text-emerald-400\">01 CENTRAL</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>\"Create snapshot\"</strong> (lightning icon). That‚Äôs it!</li></ol></div><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 pt-4\"><div class=\"bg-red-500/5 p-4 rounded border border-red-500/10\"><h4 class=\"font-bold text-red-400 mb-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider\">‚ö†Ô∏è Restore data</h4><p class=\"text-xs text-slate-400\">If a file is missing, go to <strong>02 RESTORE</strong>. Choose the date and click \"Restore\". <br><br><strong>WARNING:</strong> The whole folder will be reset to that older state. New files might get lost!</p></div><div class=\"bg-blue-500/5 p-4 rounded border border-blue-500/10\"><h4 class=\"font-bold text-blue-400 mb-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider\">üí° Save space with Analytics</h4><p class=\"text-xs text-slate-400\">In <strong>04 ANALYTICS</strong> the program searches for duplicate files. If you delete them before the backup, backups are faster and need less space.</p></div></div></div>",
  "handbook.sectionDivider": "<div class=\"h-px bg-white flex-1\"></div><span class=\"text-xs uppercase tracking-widest\">Knowledge & Details</span><div class=\"h-px bg-white flex-1\"></div>",
  "handbook.sectionDetails": "<div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">01</span> What is a snapshot?</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">A \"snapshot\" is like a photo of your data at a specific point in time. Backup Pro packs all your files into one package (ZIP file). Later you can restore exactly this state.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">02</span> Cleanup rule (retention)</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">So that your disk does not get full, Backup Pro automatically deletes very old backups. Under \"Parameters\" ‚Üí \"Retention limit\" you define how many backups you want to keep (for example the last 10). The oldest one is removed automatically.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">03</span> Workspace delta (new)</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">In <strong>01 CENTRAL</strong> you can now see the \"workspace delta\". It shows live how many files and how much space (MB/GB) changed compared to the last backup. Watch the mode in the top right (LOCAL, UPLOAD, DOWNLOAD).</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">04</span> Cloud safe & SFTP</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">Under <strong>03 CLOUD</strong> you control your remote backups. Choose between \"Upload\" (local ‚Üí cloud) and \"Download\" (cloud ‚Üí local). New: with SFTP you can create folders directly on the server via \"Create location\". For downloads you can define a dedicated local target folder.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">05</span> Troubleshooting</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">If a backup fails, most of the time a file is still open (for example an Excel sheet). Close all programs and try again. Also check whether the USB stick is full.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">06</span> System health (traffic light)</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">The \"system health\" card in the central view works like a traffic light. Green is great. Yellow means \"okay\". Red means \"attention\". If it is red you should urgently run a backup or free disk space.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">07</span> Snapshot inspector & lock</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">Click on a backup in the list to see details. <strong class=\"text-emerald-400\">New:</strong> In the \"Content\" tab you see all files inside the ZIP without restoring them. With the <strong class=\"text-amber-500\">lock icon</strong> you can protect important backups ‚Äì they will never be deleted automatically, even when the limit is reached.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">08</span> Deep scan (integrity)</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">In the inspector you will find the button <strong class=\"text-emerald-400\">CHECK INTEGRITY</strong>. This is a health check: the application recomputes the digital fingerprint (hash) and compares it. This way you can immediately see whether files on disk have become corrupted (bit rot).</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">09</span> History & log scale</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">The history lists all backups. New: with the <strong>LOG SCALE</strong> switch above the chart you can make very small backups visible next to huge ones. Use the \"Sort\" button to order the list by date or size.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">10</span> Databases (cloud dump)</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">In the cloud tab you can configure automatic backups of your MySQL or PostgreSQL databases. They are exported as SQL files and stored safely in your backup target.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">11</span> Notifications</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">Backup Pro informs you about important events directly in the interface. Errors are highlighted in red, successful actions in green. Check the log (terminal) in the central view regularly.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">12</span> System health details</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">Move the mouse over the \"system health\" card to see detailed information. The new view breaks down your score precisely in percent: <strong>COV</strong> (coverage), <strong>REC</strong> (recoverability) and <strong>DSK</strong> (disk space).</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">13</span> Advanced statistics</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">The \"total volume\" and \"backups\" cards now show more details: average snapshot size, time since the last backup and backup frequency per day. Tooltips explain further details when you hover over them.</p></div><div class=\"handbook-item p-6 bg-[#0f111a] rounded-xl border border-white/5 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all group\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors\"><span class=\"text-blue-500/50 mr-2\">14</span> Activity chart</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed\">The chart in the central view now visually distinguishes between days with a backup (filled points) and days without a backup (empty points). New grid lines and improved axes help you spot gaps in your backup strategy more quickly.</p></div>",
  "handbook.proTips": "<h4 class=\"text-xs font-black uppercase text-blue-400 mb-4 tracking-widest\">Pro tips</h4><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-[11px] mono text-slate-400\"><ul class=\"space-y-3\"><li class=\"flex gap-2\"><span class=\"text-blue-500\">>></span> <span>Create a backup before every Windows update or major change. Better safe than sorry.</span></li><li class=\"flex gap-2\"><span class=\"text-blue-500\">>></span> <span>Remember: a restore makes everything like it was before. Copy important new files somewhere else first!</span></li></ul><ul class=\"space-y-3\"><li class=\"flex gap-2\"><span class=\"text-blue-500\">>></span> <span>In the parameters you can set an \"interval\" (for example 60 minutes). Then you do not need to press anything.</span></li><li class=\"flex gap-2\"><span class=\"text-blue-500\">>></span> <span>Icons: yellow shield = \"file changed\", red cross = \"file deleted\", green plus = \"new file\".</span></li></ul></div>",
  "handbook.support": "<div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6\"><div class=\"flex-1\"><h4 class=\"text-xs font-black uppercase text-yellow-400 mb-2 tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2\"><span>‚òï</span> Support development</h4><p class=\"text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed\">Do you like <strong>Backup OS Pro</strong>? Help to push development forward! <span class=\"text-slate-500 block text-xs mt-1\">Every contribution goes directly into new features and updates.</span></p></div><a href=\"https://buymeacoffee.com/exulizer\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"group relative shrink-0\"><div class=\"absolute -inset-1 bg-yellow-400 rounded-lg opacity-20 group-hover:opacity-40 blur transition duration-200\"></div><img src=\"https://cdn.buymeacoffee.com/buttons/v2/default-yellow.png\" alt=\"Buy Me A Coffee\" class=\"relative block h-12 w-auto transform group-hover:scale-105 transition-all duration-200\" style=\"height: 50px !important;\"></a></div>",
